cs.CR, cs.HC, cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.IR 

The paper discusses the understanding, awareness, and acceptance of biometrics by the general public, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper also captures qualitative data on participants' definition of biometrics, which relates to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The use of thematic analysis and automated Word Vector analysis also suggests a focus on natural language processing (cs.CY) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper discusses the limitations of participants' awareness of emerging areas of biometrics, which could be relevant to social and information sciences (cs.SI).
